  "prompt": "When does it make sense to purchase travel insurance?",
  "response": "Here are some situations where travel insurance can be beneficial:\n\n1. Expensive trips\n- High-cost vacations with significant upfront expenses\n- International travel\n- Cruises or tour packages\n\n2. Destinations with potential risks\n- Areas with political instability\n- Regions prone to natural disasters\n- Countries with healthcare challenges\n\n3. Non-refundable bookings\n- Prepaid tours\n- Expensive flights\n- Non-refundable accommodations\n\n4. Health and personal circumstances\n- Traveling with medical conditions\n- Elderly travelers\n- Trips during peak flu or pandemic seasons\n- When your regular health insurance doesn't cover international care\n\n5. Adventure or high-risk activities\n- Extreme sports\n- Wilderness expeditions\n- Activities with potential injury risks\n\n6. Specific scenarios\n- Potential trip cancellation due to work or family emergencies\n- Connections to remote destinations\n- Traveling during hurricane/storm seasons\n\n7. When insurance is relatively inexpensive\n- Cost is low compared to overall trip expenses\n- Provides peace of mind\n- Covers potential significant financial losses\n\nFactors to consider:\n- Compare different insurance plans\n- Read policy details carefully\n- Check existing credit card or personal insurance coverage\n- Understand specific exclusions and limitations",
